Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.73,0:00:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I suppose I should be happy that I'm back again, but the one thing that you got
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.53,0:00:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to be happy about is something else, one damn happy thing after another.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.49,0:00:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't even be miserable anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.13,0:00:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, how can I get over being miserable?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.92,0:00:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, don't get over it, just be happy, learn how to love being miserable.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.71,0:00:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Lots of people do.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.71,0:00:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it's just horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.32,0:01:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you agree with them, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.98,0:01:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.98,0:01:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It is horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.98,0:01:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so we're talking about the roads to happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.95,0:01:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stop and examine yourself, you begin to wonder what are your goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.68,0:01:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't know what your goals are, it's fun to just sit down and write them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.09,0:01:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What are my goals in this life?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.34,0:01:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people here know what their goals are in this life?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.59,0:01:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people have written them down?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.01,0:01:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Written them down?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.01,0:01:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh boy, oh boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.56,0:01:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to make them more conscious, you actually write them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.95,0:01:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,My goal in this life is, boom, and then you can prioritize them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.35,0:02:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, one good goal is to be happy no matter what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.04,0:02:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Then if you win, you say, hooray, I won, and then if you lose, you say, thank God, I lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.47,0:02:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll come up with some of the reasons for that later in this list.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.53,0:02:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's much better.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.69,0:02:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it's much better to lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.86,0:02:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, being rich and famous seems to be an obsession with the television industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.78,0:02:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Rich and famous is what they feed on.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.84,0:02:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Rich and famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.63,0:02:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So how to differentiate the flimsy ones such as rich and famous from mature goals?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.24,0:02:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Be pleased with the direction you're going instead of where you are with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.43,0:02:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Be pleased with the direction, your alignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.56,0:02:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of saying, I won't be happy until I reach there,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.91,0:03:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,or I won't be happy until I have $84,000 saved up,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.68,0:03:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,just be happy that you are in the direction of trying to be thrifty
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.56,0:03:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and think about your older age and provide for it, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.00,0:03:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So be happy that you are in a certain direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.86,0:03:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, spiritual work, that is very much so,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.31,0:03:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's no way you can actually really tell where you're at
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.19,0:03:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in your spiritual evolution.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.34,0:03:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But to be happy with the fact that your direction is to achieve enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.12,0:03:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,or salvation, to bring about good for others and happiness to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.52,0:03:50.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So be happy with the things that you have assigned a value to,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.96,0:03:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to be friendlies.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.77,0:03:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,To be friendly and cheerful, to be uplifting to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.27,0:03:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've always tried to be uplifting to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.84,0:04:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,When people are depressed, I clown around them and get them to laugh
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.71,0:04:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and make life as easy as you can for other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.86,0:04:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And so be pleased with the direction that you have chosen for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.87,0:04:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the direction you're in and not how far you are along the path.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.79,0:04:24.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that you're on the path is what's significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.61,0:04:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,How far you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.67,0:04:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, as anybody's guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.42,0:04:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're talking about practical reality versus fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.51,0:04:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, we know that these symbols of Hollywood success
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.69,0:04:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and TV star success are, you know, symbolic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.51,0:04:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And that it actually has to do with we project value onto it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.98,0:04:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And that energy, as described by Alice Bailey, is called glamour.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.18,0:04:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't that that person...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.80,0:04:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,has that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.16,0:05:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that you have projected desirability onto that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.06,0:05:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You have projected desirability onto that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.51,0:05:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In and of itself, it has no attraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.17,0:05:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.12,0:05:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.08,0:05:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing in this world has any attraction
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.31,0:05:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you project attractiveness to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.26,0:05:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that attribute that you have projected onto it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.58,0:05:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.57,0:05:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that makes it desirable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.05,0:05:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're like a dog chasing its tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.38,0:05:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're like a dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.61,0:05:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So most people in the world are like dogs chasing their tails.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.75,0:05:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They have decided that that is success.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.55,0:05:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,My dog does it all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.75,0:05:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.32,0:05:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,She starts to chase her tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.31,0:05:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,She all of a sudden, you see her go...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.69,0:05:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, why are you chasing your tail?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.00,0:06:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,She goes, Kelsey, stop chasing your tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.81,0:06:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,For a minute, she thought it was something out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.79,0:06:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's not out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.93,0:06:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just me I'm chasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.81,0:06:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, it was more fun when I thought
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.49,0:06:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,it was something out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.94,0:06:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.91,0:06:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.62,0:06:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So chasing your tail, then, is because you've
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.00,0:06:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,projected wonderment upon that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.35,0:06:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Thing is to pursue a thing because that is what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.85,0:06:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're studious, then being a studious person
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.37,0:06:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.60,0:06:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.42,0:06:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And the thing is to enjoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.87,0:06:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.00,0:06:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.10,0:06:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy the process of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.39,0:06:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Enjoy the various stages of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.07,0:06:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fun to be a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.48,0:06:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's exciting to be an adolescent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.00,0:06:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's great to be a young adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.91,0:07:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Middle age has a lot of wonderful things about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.25,0:07:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Older age is self-rewarding.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.44,0:07:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You're too old to give a rap about it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.63,0:07:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But other people worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.77,0:07:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm dying for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.62,0:07:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, yep, I remember when I used to think that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.39,0:07:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep, yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.22,0:07:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So you joined the yep generation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.22,0:07:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.30,0:07:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a million bucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.33,0:07:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep, I remember when that was a big deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.20,0:07:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.48,0:07:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So in other words, what's happening
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.16,0:07:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,is due to your own choice and your own decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.54,0:07:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That puts you back in control.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.86,0:07:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Puts you back in control to realize that where you are is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.22,0:07:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the result of your own decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.18,0:07:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.86,0:07:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You choose and decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.87,0:07:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You've chosen and decided to go in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.73,0:08:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That way you don't end up blaming it on other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.55,0:08:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because no matter which way you go, there are risks involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.38,0:08:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that not so?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.30,0:08:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if you decide to stay home and sit in your chair
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.93,0:08:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and not go anywhere, you will then become decrepit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.54,0:08:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Decrepit, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.87,0:08:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, move on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.51,0:08:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got 101.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.60,0:08:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got to move along.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.25,0:08:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,To be flexible versus rigid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.64,0:08:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,To be flexible, like the reed that bends in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.26,0:08:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The reed, the current.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.63,0:08:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So the reed that bends with the current is flexible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.22,0:08:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The one which is stiff and inflexible
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.34,0:08:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is broken by the current.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.70,0:08:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's an old Taoist teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.84,0:08:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an old Taoist teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.87,0:08:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,To be flexible and to bend with the wind
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.62,0:08:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and to bend with the current rather than break.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.75,0:09:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,To be able to change, to switch roles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.17,0:09:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You can also see your life as a sequence of roles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.17,0:09:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not only what you are, but you
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.01,0:09:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,are fulfilling a certain social role.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.98,0:09:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The parent or the child, those are all roles.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.47,0:09:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we learn not to be flexible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.37,0:09:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we learn not to be flexible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.83,0:09:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we learn not to be flexible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.87,0:09:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we learn not to be flexible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.07,0:09:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to put happiness dependent on anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.75,0:09:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be happy if I get an A in this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.05,0:09:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so you have to cancel and then I'll be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.05,0:09:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that your happiness is not
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.90,0:09:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,provisional about anything, except the direction
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.62,0:09:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're going.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.41,0:09:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I'm going in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.67,0:09:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm choosing spiritual evolution as a lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.87,0:09:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm choosing spiritual evolution as a lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.44,0:09:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives my life meaning and greater significance
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.32,0:10:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in serving God in every way that I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.19,0:10:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,One way to serve God is by being happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.91,0:10:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,God's will for you is happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.89,0:10:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, to be happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.19,0:10:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it's sort of just a style of languaging,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.52,0:10:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is pleasing to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.47,0:10:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There's this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.70,0:10:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.98,0:10:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So God's demand is that you be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.16,0:10:34.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody here refuse to be happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.27,0:10:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody wants to go to the lower places?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.98,0:10:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So being happy is fulfilling your human potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.23,0:10:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're created in that style by Almighty God.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.00,0:10:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So make the happiness independent of phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.50,0:11:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, you don't have to clutch and grasp at things.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.48,0:11:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Clutching and grasping at things, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.84,0:11:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is a good way to lose them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.80,0:11:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Clarify your goals and your ideals.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.38,0:11:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm surprised how many people here
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.50,0:11:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,raised their hands that they have actually sat down
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.50,0:11:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and listed what their goals are and prioritized them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.84,0:11:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, in actual life,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.02,0:11:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,we're doing that all the time, but it's unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.59,0:11:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We're choosing and choosing one goal over another,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.95,0:11:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.19,0:11:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But to make them conscious and intellectually aware
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.90,0:11:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is of great value.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.04,0:11:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that all value that you attribute to anything
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.30,0:11:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.64,0:11:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you value it doesn't mean that it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.21,0:11:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It just means that you value it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.62,0:11:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The only value that I would say is independent of personal opinion
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.60,0:11:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is the scale of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.87,0:12:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The scale of consciousness indicates
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.44,0:12:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,on a mathematical, arithmetic level,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.37,0:12:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,value when looked at from the viewpoint of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.27,0:12:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But many people would disregard that as of any value.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.15,0:12:20.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So even that which is a confirmatory value
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.82,0:12:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,would not be valuable in another person's eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.27,0:12:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Honesty and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.63,0:12:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Honesty and integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.20,0:12:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in our culture, honesty and integrity are virtues.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.38,0:12:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There are other cultures in which honesty,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.16,0:12:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and integrity is idiotic and stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.24,0:12:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other side of the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.88,0:12:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,if the price of this object is $6,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.92,0:12:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and you sell it for $6,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.69,0:12:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,they can see you an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.70,0:12:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Honesty and integrity,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.37,0:12:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,in a different culture,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.91,0:13:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is considered stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.87,0:13:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how do you accommodate yourself to a culture
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.36,0:13:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that thinks that truth, honesty, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.62,0:13:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is a defect?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.48,0:13:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.29,0:13:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a little hard to figure how you're going to accommodate
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.30,0:13:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to something that is diametrically opposed
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.94,0:13:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to your own set of values.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.79,0:13:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.90,0:13:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Clarify goals and ideals.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.25,0:13:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that all value is arbitrary.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.01,0:13:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There are huge cultures in which
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.44,0:13:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,honesty is considered stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.63,0:13:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.67,0:13:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Honesty is stupidity.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.20,0:13:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.10,0:13:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.01,0:13:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.48,0:13:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, a nap on a train or a plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.72,0:13:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, ha, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.48,0:13:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought I'd put some quickies in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.50,0:13:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.11,0:13:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.12,0:14:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You put up your feet and have a quick nap,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.66,0:14:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're happy no matter where you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.85,0:14:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.83,0:14:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.73,0:14:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.30,0:14:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got 101 to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.40,0:14:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We better move along.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.60,0:14:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Live one day at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.50,0:14:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the 12-step,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.62,0:14:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the 12-step program
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.09,0:14:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of the greatest sources of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.99,0:14:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,People who practice the 12-step program
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.58,0:14:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,are happier than other people,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.20,0:14:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can even calibrate them
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.70,0:14:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are actually happier.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.79,0:14:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,They actually live in the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.00,0:14:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And one of the axioms
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.44,0:14:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is to live one day at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.28,0:14:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that rational?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.83,0:14:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, yesterday's gone forever,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.59,0:14:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,so it has no reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.19,0:14:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow isn't here yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.64,0:14:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,so it has no reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.57,0:14:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the only thing that's really real
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.57,0:14:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,is what's right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.96,0:14:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, living one day at a time,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.63,0:14:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is a very important part
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.41,0:14:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of the 12-step program.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.34,0:14:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the 12-step program
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.94,0:14:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates around 570,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.46,0:14:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's higher than any other
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.86,0:15:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,pathway currently available.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.45,0:15:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, be lucky if,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.19,0:15:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you're lucky if you have something
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.42,0:15:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that requires you to go to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.80,0:15:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and join the 12-step program.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.59,0:15:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you haven't got a problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.16,0:15:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you better go get one
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.19,0:15:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so you can go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.47,0:15:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can live one day at a time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.35,0:15:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what comes up,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.39,0:15:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, well, that was yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.36,0:15:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And yesterday, I thought,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.22,0:15:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,what will I talk about tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.29,0:15:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,at the lecture?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.87,0:15:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, well, I'll worry about that
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.94,0:15:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,when tomorrow gets here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.49,0:15:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is a cat's purr
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.09,0:15:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or a dog's wagging tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.61,0:15:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We calibrated them at 500 and something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.90,0:15:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A cat's purr.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.85,0:15:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to be angry, upset,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.59,0:15:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and self-pity
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.66,0:15:43.88,Default,,0,0,0,,when a kitty's purring in your arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.57,0:15:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You get this kitty,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.52,0:15:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and she's going,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.76,0:15:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,purr, purr, purr, purr.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.47,0:15:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a cat at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.28,0:15:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I paid 50 bucks for this cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.09,0:15:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's my $50 cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.17,0:16:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Named Bootsy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.36,0:16:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, no matter what I do,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.75,0:16:05.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Bootsy wants to participate.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.65,0:16:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I have to do the checkbook,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.05,0:16:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,balance the checkbook at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.84,0:16:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And he loves the checkbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.34,0:16:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute I get it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.30,0:16:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,he claims the checkbook to be his.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.01,0:16:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to feel unhappy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.48,0:16:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, give me back my checkbook.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.53,0:16:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Happiness is a cat's purr.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.50,0:16:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing nicer than hearing kitties purring.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.66,0:16:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And sometimes I come home,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.92,0:16:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's all three kitties sitting around.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.95,0:16:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All three of them are purring.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.25,0:16:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Purr, purr, purr, purr, purr, purr, purr.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.69,0:16:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.37,0:16:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you get,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.23,0:16:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,all three of them purring.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.95,0:16:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the three of them are there purring,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.61,0:16:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in the meantime,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.38,0:16:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,down on the kitchen floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.64,0:16:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the dog's tail is wagging.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.51,0:16:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it's very hard to be unhappy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.27,0:16:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Three kitties purring at once,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.01,0:16:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and the dog wagging his tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.62,0:16:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that makes you happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.57,0:16:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is your wife's voice comes over and says,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.75,0:16:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,dinner's ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.80,0:17:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you've got the ultimate happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.43,0:17:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Dinner's ready,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.41,0:17:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the cats are purring,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.63,0:17:10.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and the dog's tail is wagging.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.07,0:17:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Who could want for anything more, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.50,0:17:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Another source of happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.29,0:17:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is faith versus skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.18,0:17:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Skepticism is a narcissistic position,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.40,0:17:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and faith is a much higher position.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.44,0:17:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, faith, of course the person who is a skeptic,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.85,0:17:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,at the same time, idiotically doesn't realize,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.96,0:17:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't his skepticism,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.85,0:17:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it's his faith in his skepticism that's keeping him alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.96,0:17:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He thinks skepticism will lead me to the truth and happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.00,0:17:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's why he's a skeptic.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.00,0:17:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's his faith in his skepticism,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.00,0:17:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that gives him that feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.00,0:17:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that paradoxically funny?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.00,0:18:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if he was skeptical about his skepticism,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.54,0:18:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,he'd be making progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.15,0:18:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think too much of skepticism is the road to happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.07,0:18:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm skeptical about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.07,0:18:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have faith that my skepticism,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.00,0:18:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,a lot of skepticism,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.00,0:18:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,will lead me to happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.56,0:18:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So we learn to be grateful for what we have and what we have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.22,0:18:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Grateful for what we have and for what we have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.22,0:18:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, people say,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.67,0:18:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,are you grateful that you're older?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.17,0:18:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.26,0:18:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm grateful for my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.51,0:18:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm grateful for my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.51,0:18:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm grateful for my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.42,0:18:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say, well, considering the alternative,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.22,0:18:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,very good indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.31,0:18:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.79,0:18:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Maurice Chevalier.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.29,0:18:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Gratitude for what one has and what you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.00,0:18:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What we've learned is a result of all the effort we put in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.09,0:19:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We've traveled all those miles through life
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.09,0:19:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to become what we are at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.09,0:19:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're the product of the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.13,0:19:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can build upon the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.02,0:19:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're also attracted by the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.82,0:19:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we are in no man's land between the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.48,0:19:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which is over,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.07,0:19:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.77,0:19:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,which isn't here yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.48,0:19:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.07,0:19:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You live in a complete vacuum.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.47,0:19:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The past is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.17,0:19:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The future isn't here yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.51,0:19:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Though the only place you can exist is in this present moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.01,0:19:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So the only thing you have to worry about
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.01,0:19:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is this present moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.11,0:19:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This present moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.52,0:19:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Detached versus craving.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.67,0:19:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It means if it happens, it's terrific,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.67,0:19:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and if it doesn't, it's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.90,0:19:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity to become detached is a learned technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.21,0:20:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody should practice becoming detached
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.21,0:20:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,from something you think you just have to have to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.21,0:20:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Pick something arbitrarily and start becoming detached from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.61,0:20:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, well,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.51,0:20:16.31,Default,,0,0,0,,if I become detached from it,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.42,0:20:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,then I won't get it, will I?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.01,0:20:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So the person wants to become detached
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.11,0:20:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and still be attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.72,0:20:26.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a sneaky trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.92,0:20:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and I won't let you get away with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.52,0:20:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Detached means if it happens, great,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.02,0:20:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and if it doesn't happen, fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.94,0:20:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,One way or the other, it's all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.74,0:20:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.14,0:20:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that which I am in reality
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.44,0:20:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is not going to be affected one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.24,0:20:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I've either learned how to derive happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.44,0:20:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,from my own existence, or I haven't.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.44,0:20:52.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And if I haven't learned how to derive happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.44,0:20:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,from my own existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.44,0:20:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,then what could possibly make me happier?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.21,0:21:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can't be happy worth this much,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.21,0:21:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,how will I be happier if I'm worth twice as much?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.03,0:21:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So gratitude for what one has and is,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.03,0:21:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,what you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.03,0:21:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody sitting in this audience
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.26,0:21:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is obviously in a good place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.26,0:21:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They should be grateful for what one has,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.48,0:21:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,for what they have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.48,0:21:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the searching after truth
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.48,0:21:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of its expressions
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.48,0:21:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of the most advanced states of consciousness there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.48,0:21:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,To seek truth for its own sake
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.57,0:21:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and to go wherever one has to go
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.93,0:21:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to learn truth is therefore a great goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.93,0:21:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Gratitude that you're even interested
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.93,0:21:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in integrity and truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.41,0:21:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You realize that about 98% of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.41,0:21:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is not interested in truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.41,0:21:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,One time we did an arm on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.09,0:21:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The number of people who are interested in enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.09,0:22:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if you stop them on the street,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.09,0:22:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it's less than 1 in 10 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.09,0:22:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stop everybody on the street,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.76,0:22:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,after 10 million people you'll find one person.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.96,0:22:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,My ultimate goal in this lifetime is enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.04,0:22:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.04,0:22:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That's still the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.04,0:22:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.91,0:22:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Desiring enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.51,0:22:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,are 1 in 10 million on the street.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.51,0:22:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha said,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.94,0:22:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,rare it is,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.94,0:22:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,great good karma
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.96,0:22:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to have heard of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.96,0:22:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The first great good karma
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.18,0:22:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you have heard of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.46,0:22:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The second is that you decide to pursue it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.46,0:22:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Having heard of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.58,0:22:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you decide to pursue it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.88,0:22:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And rarest of all
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.88,0:22:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is to pursue it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.77,0:23:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and achieve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.13,0:23:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So the Buddha said, therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.13,0:23:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that you in this audience
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.42,0:23:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,are rare indeed
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.42,0:23:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in good karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.42,0:23:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody in this audience
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.42,0:23:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,has good karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.42,0:23:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.77,0:23:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.72,0:23:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, happy, happy Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.39,0:23:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddha says, my God, they heard me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.28,0:23:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, fortunate is the Buddha
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.08,0:23:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,who has followers to listen to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.11,0:23:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.11,0:23:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that, this is like,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.15,0:23:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the Buddha that's happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.30,0:23:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's that Buddha that's lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.53,0:23:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,How many Buddhas have people
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.53,0:23:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,who pay any attention to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.99,0:23:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I always say.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.10,0:24:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.74,0:24:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I like the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.74,0:24:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Gratitude for what one has and is.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.97,0:24:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Detachment versus craving.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.05,0:24:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So to become enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.96,0:24:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,enlightenment is the releasing
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.96,0:24:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,of attachments and aversions
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.96,0:24:16.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore of cravings.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.96,0:24:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So the entrapment into the body
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.96,0:24:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,which initiates through the senses
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.96,0:24:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,in the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.96,0:24:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Enlightenment means becoming detached
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.96,0:24:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to letting go of craving.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.96,0:24:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,To letting go.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.15,0:24:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If it happens, it happens
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.15,0:24:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.15,0:24:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it doesn't,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.15,0:24:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,then I'll be doing something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.44,0:24:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm not doing this this morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.44,0:24:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,then I would be doing something else this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.88,0:24:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I could be home,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.24,0:24:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and the kitties could be purring,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.24,0:24:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and the dog wagging his tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.48,0:24:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.14,0:24:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Detached versus craving.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.13,0:25:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Craving is always putting a desiringness.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.13,0:25:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Craving is always wanting something
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.93,0:25:04.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have glamorized
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.93,0:25:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and said,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.93,0:25:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that will make me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.93,0:25:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole attitude of life is,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.78,0:25:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is the glass half full
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.78,0:25:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,or is it half empty?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.78,0:25:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Optimism or pessimism?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.98,0:25:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Optimism.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.83,0:25:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Optimism and pessimism.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.83,0:25:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the glass half full
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.51,0:25:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,or half empty?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.57,0:25:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So there we're saying how
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.57,0:25:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,your perception of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.57,0:25:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,how you contextualize it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.71,0:25:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it half full or half empty?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.71,0:25:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.33,0:25:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it's half full because it's half empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.33,0:26:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.33,0:26:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it both ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.95,0:26:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,First time in history
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.13,0:26:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody won that one conundrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.13,0:26:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's half full because
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.08,0:26:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,it's half empty, idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.99,0:26:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's half empty because it's half full.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.99,0:26:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that easy?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:17.99,0:26:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It took me to come along and solve
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.51,0:26:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that conundrum.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.91,0:26:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know how the world survived without it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.91,0:26:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.34,0:26:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Detached means if I find the answer
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.34,0:26:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to something that's terrific
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.34,0:26:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and I have to let go of the craving
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.34,0:26:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,for knowing the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.34,0:26:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,When you start getting,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.38,0:26:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,investigating, researching truth
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.38,0:26:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and its various expressions,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.38,0:26:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,this can be for you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.38,0:26:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,where you begin to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.27,0:26:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,uh,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.27,0:26:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to know the answer
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.38,0:26:57.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.38,0:26:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And you drive your spouse crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.38,0:27:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,In the morning
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.75,0:27:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll come in the other end
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.75,0:27:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and she can tell I'm coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.84,0:27:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say, honey, could I have your arm one second?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.84,0:27:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.84,0:27:12.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I just have to know
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.84,0:27:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,what such and such calibrates that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.84,0:27:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I just have to know, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.84,0:27:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I just have to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.84,0:27:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I don't have to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.84,0:27:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.29,0:27:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so I realize
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.29,0:27:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not a have to, it's a want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.29,0:27:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Want to. Intellectual curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.33,0:27:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, intellectual curiosity
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.33,0:27:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is what drove the whole renaissance.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.33,0:27:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.33,0:27:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So a great deal of wisdom
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.33,0:27:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,comes out of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.33,0:27:44.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, it's sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.43,0:27:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,a positive curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.43,0:27:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The optimist thinks
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.45,0:27:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that increasing one's
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.45,0:27:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level will increase
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.45,0:27:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,one's happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.45,0:27:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's optimistic
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.34,0:28:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but also fulfillable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.30,0:28:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And in order to do that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.30,0:28:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we choose spiritual versus
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.30,0:28:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,material goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.47,0:28:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Because spiritual goals are
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.47,0:28:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot be lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.00,0:28:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual goals are
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.00,0:28:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,valuable beyond all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.10,0:28:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And beyond the physical.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.10,0:28:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Material goals come and go.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.46,0:28:22.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The morning you get up and you turn on
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.46,0:28:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,the Rasmussen Report
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.58,0:28:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,or what is that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.58,0:28:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Something report. Tells you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.58,0:28:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,where you lost money yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.58,0:28:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well yesterday it had all these famous people
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.06,0:28:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that are multi-millionaires.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.06,0:28:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And how much they lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.06,0:28:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They all lost 25% of their money.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.06,0:28:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And anyway, that won't affect
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.45,0:28:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,their happiness because the capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.45,0:28:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to make more money is there.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.45,0:28:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's the capacity then,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.79,0:28:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity and not the thing itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.79,0:28:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual versus material goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.56,0:28:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now these are the things
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.56,0:28:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.67,0:29:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The things that we surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.67,0:29:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.56,0:29:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are the things
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.56,0:29:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that we surrender to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.56,0:29:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender those things of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.73,0:29:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to mammon
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.73,0:29:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which is
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.75,0:29:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of spiritual to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.75,0:29:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And not confuse the two.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.75,0:29:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender that which is God's
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.01,0:29:20.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to God and that which is material
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.01,0:29:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to mammon.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.10,0:29:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible says.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.10,0:29:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.77,0:29:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The surrendering
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.51,0:29:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to God's will
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.51,0:29:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is a sophisticated
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.42,0:29:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.60,0:29:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,really evolves
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.41,0:29:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,with your own level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.41,0:29:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,As your own level
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.41,0:29:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness evolves,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.73,0:29:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the understanding of God's
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.73,0:29:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,will becomes
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.89,0:29:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,progressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.69,0:29:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And can't really be described
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.69,0:29:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,verbatim as it progresses.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.88,0:29:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you're a kid
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.88,0:30:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you think God's will is that you go to church.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.88,0:30:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't use
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.07,0:30:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,certain bad words
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.07,0:30:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and various things.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.98,0:30:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So your understanding of what is God's will
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.98,0:30:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,evolves
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.98,0:30:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,over the decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.98,0:30:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally becomes almost
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.00,0:30:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't really explain it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.00,0:30:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more contextualized.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.00,0:30:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A contextualized knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.00,0:30:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.00,0:30:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that at this moment
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.17,0:30:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in this instant
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.17,0:30:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in this evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.17,0:30:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is the way to go
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.23,0:30:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.23,0:30:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So a certain knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.13,0:30:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,evolves
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.20,0:30:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and we call it wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.20,0:30:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A certain spiritual wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.20,0:30:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,To surrender to God's will
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.35,0:30:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,then brings about
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.74,0:30:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,an evolution of one's wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.74,0:30:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it God's will that I
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.79,0:30:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,take up arms and fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.79,0:30:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is it God's will that I surrender?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.79,0:30:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether to take up arms
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.55,0:31:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,against the slings and arrows
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.55,0:31:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of outrageous fortune
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.77,0:31:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,or battle them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.90,0:31:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is really
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.25,0:31:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,a conflict of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.25,0:31:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,not a conflict but a conundrum
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.25,0:31:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,which is permanent.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.33,0:31:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In all the evolutionary phases
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.44,0:31:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of life
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.44,0:31:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,what does it mean to surrender to God's will
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.44,0:31:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,at that point?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.44,0:31:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,For some people to surrender to God's will
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.53,0:31:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,means to obey
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.53,0:31:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the command and shoot
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.53,0:31:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.66,0:31:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,For another person to surrender to God's will
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.66,0:31:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,means I cannot kill another human
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.66,0:31:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,under any circumstance.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.66,0:31:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is God's will?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.32,0:31:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're 18
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.76,0:31:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're in the Navy
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.76,0:31:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and they say shoot them
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.22,0:31:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,God's will is that you shoot them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.82,0:31:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're 82
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.82,0:31:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and they say shoot them
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.82,0:31:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you say I'm not going to shoot them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.81,0:31:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So what is God's will?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.24,0:32:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It means for you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.68,0:32:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,at this time in this context
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.68,0:32:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so truth cannot be
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.68,0:32:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,defined unless
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.80,0:32:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you define it within the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.80,0:32:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,In what circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.80,0:32:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.05,0:32:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it evil to do this
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.05,0:32:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,or not to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.50,0:32:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,To retrospectively make things
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.50,0:32:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that were done under threat of war
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.50,0:32:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,illegal
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.50,0:32:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is like an outrage to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.50,0:32:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,this violation
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.50,0:32:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of God's will
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.50,0:32:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,because what's truth
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.50,0:32:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and what's God's will
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.50,0:32:36.41,Default,,0,0,0,,truth is dependent
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.50,0:32:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,on circumstance
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.50,0:32:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,on context.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.50,0:32:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What's true in this context
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.50,0:32:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is a lie in this context.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.44,0:32:46.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And fulfilling your obligation
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.44,0:32:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to mankind and God here
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.44,0:32:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,is a violation of it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.44,0:32:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.82,0:32:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,where spiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.82,0:32:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,leads to progressive
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.82,0:32:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,sophistication.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.18,0:33:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What is God's will for you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.18,0:33:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,at this moment
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.18,0:33:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in these circumstances?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.49,0:33:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If you were older then
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.49,0:33:10.39,Default,,0,0,0,,it would be different.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.49,0:33:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If you were younger it would be different.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.51,0:33:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're not older and you're not younger
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.51,0:33:16.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you're who you are right at this moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.42,0:33:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the highest
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.42,0:33:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,thing that you can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.42,0:33:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Serve your country
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.42,0:33:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,or become a conscientious
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.42,0:33:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,objector.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.42,0:33:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You know I practiced psychiatry
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.42,0:33:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for many years, 50 years
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.42,0:33:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and I forget what war it was, Vietnam I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.42,0:33:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Lots of people wanted to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.42,0:33:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,had to be seen by me and
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.42,0:33:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,whether they were
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.76,0:33:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,capable, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.76,0:33:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And the question I always
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.76,0:33:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,was run up against was
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.79,0:33:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,if you don't want to go
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.70,0:33:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,to Vietnam and kill anybody
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.70,0:33:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say well you can
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.70,0:33:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you got two options.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.70,0:33:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You can move to Canada
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.70,0:33:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,or you can just become a conscientious objector.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.70,0:33:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Just be a conscientious objector.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.70,0:34:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And that solved it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.70,0:34:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't have to be
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.70,0:34:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,anti something.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.70,0:34:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You can find a livable
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.70,0:34:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,space in which you can live.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.69,0:34:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You can serve your country
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.69,0:34:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and be a conscientious objector
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.98,0:34:15.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can work in the stock room
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.98,0:34:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't have to shoot people
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.88,0:34:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so right now I'd say
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.13,0:34:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,no I can't shoot people now
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.13,0:34:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it's just don't work out for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.13,0:34:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't stand all the noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.13,0:34:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll lead a prayer group
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.13,0:34:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in the back while you folks
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.67,0:34:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,go ahead and do the shooting part.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.67,0:34:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're done shooting
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.67,0:34:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,let me know.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.92,0:34:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity to let go then
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.92,0:34:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.92,0:34:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Capacity to surrender to God's will
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.92,0:34:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,increases the capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.50,0:34:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.50,0:34:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,To let go is
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.40,0:34:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,progressively more and more easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.96,0:34:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you let go of anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.96,0:34:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually you reach the point
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.96,0:35:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,where you can really let go of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.96,0:35:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean let go seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.44,0:35:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You can overlook things
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.44,0:35:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you can skip things
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.44,0:35:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but a very serious let go
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.44,0:35:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning really let go
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.44,0:35:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes progressively easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.44,0:35:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.63,0:35:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,very nice
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.63,0:35:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that it is that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.63,0:35:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender to God's will then
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.71,0:35:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is the capacity to let go
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.71,0:35:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and when we
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.76,0:35:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.17,0:35:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we surrender our love
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.17,0:35:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,our self to God
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.17,0:35:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,out of love for God
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.21,0:35:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore the capacity to let go
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.21,0:35:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,is almost infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.88,0:35:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If people say I can't do a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.88,0:35:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.94,0:35:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't let go of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.94,0:35:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say now if I hold the gun to your head
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.94,0:35:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you don't let go
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.94,0:35:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to blow your brains out.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.13,0:35:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly they can let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.48,0:35:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So you understand letting go
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.38,0:35:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,anything you think you're caught with
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.61,0:36:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can't let go of it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.61,0:36:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,you picture a gun at your head
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.28,0:36:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.28,0:36:07.19,Default,,0,0,0,,now can you let go of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.28,0:36:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody stuck on something
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.73,0:36:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,they can't let go of?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.36,0:36:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey did I bring the gun this morning or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.36,0:36:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If we hold the gun to your head
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.00,0:36:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it's amazing you can let go of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.00,0:36:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright so
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.82,0:36:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you be pleased with your own progress
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.82,0:36:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity to let go is there
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.82,0:36:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't can you
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.82,0:36:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,it's will you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.82,0:36:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a matter of the human will.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.92,0:36:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You say I can't let go of it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.01,0:36:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the minute you hear yourself saying
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.01,0:36:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let go of that
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.01,0:36:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,tell yourself the truth is
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.01,0:36:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't let go of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.01,0:36:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay you won't let go of it
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.01,0:36:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that puts it in a different domain
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.01,0:36:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because something you can't let go of today
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.01,0:36:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you may be able to a week from now
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.01,0:36:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a year from now or a decade
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.01,0:37:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,a decade from now
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.13,0:37:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it's easy to let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.13,0:37:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Being a movie star is hard to let go of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.13,0:37:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,as an adolescent fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.13,0:37:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But by 80 you've gotten over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.15,0:37:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm pleased with my progress
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.15,0:37:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to want to be Clark Gable anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.15,0:37:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Clark Gable was our hero
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.51,0:37:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,when I grew up you know
Dialogue: 0,0:37:25.51,0:37:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,if you could only be Clark Gable
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.78,0:37:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,so you don't have to be Clark Gable now
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.78,0:37:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.92,0:37:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And you avoid self-judgment
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.92,0:37:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,now we said the self-judgment
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.92,0:37:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is the internalized parent
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.92,0:37:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you see there's the child in you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.82,0:37:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,there's the child
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.19,0:37:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and then judgmentalism
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.19,0:37:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is the inner parent
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.19,0:37:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the super ego
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.19,0:37:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is constantly judging everything you do
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.46,0:37:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,how to handle that inner judge
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.46,0:37:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,all the time
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.51,0:37:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,so the child
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.51,0:37:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,if you want to enjoy life
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.51,0:38:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the child has to stay alive
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.51,0:38:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to have a child
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.63,0:38:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,it's handy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.80,0:38:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,child come here
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.78,0:38:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to sit on my child all the time
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.69,0:38:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the child wants to take over everything
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.69,0:38:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they're not going to take you seriously
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.55,0:38:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,if you're so childish
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.55,0:38:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you're right you're right yes
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.67,0:38:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I must be serious
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.51,0:38:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and dignified
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.88,0:38:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I did it
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.13,0:38:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,whew
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.65,0:38:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that takes care of the kids
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.09,0:38:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,having your inner kid alive and well
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.28,0:38:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,is part of happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.28,0:38:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you can sit on the kid
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.46,0:38:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,periodically
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.46,0:39:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,when he's in the street car
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.46,0:39:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or something
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.46,0:39:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to go with my younger sister
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.46,0:39:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'd have to be with her
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.55,0:39:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,on the street car
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.59,0:39:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I was like 10 or 11
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.59,0:39:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and she was like 7 or something
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.71,0:39:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,so I'd say now you sit next to your brother
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.71,0:39:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,so she'd be very good
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.71,0:39:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'd get on the street car
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.71,0:39:21.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and she'd be sitting next to me
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.71,0:39:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and next thing you know
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.71,0:39:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,she'd start wandering down the aisle
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.82,0:39:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,of the street car
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.82,0:39:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,then she's running up and down the aisle
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.82,0:39:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,laughing and giggling and running up and down
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.82,0:39:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'd pretend I didn't know her
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.86,0:39:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I would shrink down with shame and embarrassment
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.67,0:39:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,laughs
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.94,0:39:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,laughs
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.38,0:39:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.92,0:39:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so she was being bad
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.92,0:39:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was being good
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.03,0:39:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,so to me
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.03,0:40:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,being good was the way to happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.03,0:40:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and for her doing
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.98,0:40:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,what the hell she wanted
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.98,0:40:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,was her way to happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.98,0:40:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,laughs
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.17,0:40:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,see I can't wait to see my sister again
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.17,0:40:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,on the other side
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.17,0:40:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,she was adorable
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.17,0:40:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,just loved her to pieces
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.17,0:40:20.07,Default,,0,0,0,,but she loved being bad
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.17,0:40:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,laughs
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.17,0:40:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,why was it bad
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.17,0:40:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,because it was on the street car
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.17,0:40:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and my mother said
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.17,0:40:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you're supposed to sit in your seats
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.17,0:40:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and not run up and down the aisle
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.26,0:40:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in the street car
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.26,0:40:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,made it good or bad
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.26,0:40:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,alright therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.36,0:40:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,our human values
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.36,0:40:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to win is provisional
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.36,0:40:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you mean by win
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.36,0:40:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you know many times we see people
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.36,0:40:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing something that to them is a win
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.36,0:40:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and we see it as a loss
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.36,0:40:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or vice versa
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.36,0:40:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,so what is a win
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.36,0:40:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is how you define it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.36,0:40:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,how you contextualize it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.78,0:41:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's a win or a loss
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.78,0:41:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is dependent upon the circumstances
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.78,0:41:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,simplicity versus
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.09,0:41:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,complexity
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.09,0:41:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is really super complex
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.09,0:41:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is harder to achieve
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.09,0:41:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,than that which is simple
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.63,0:41:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore one way
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.63,0:41:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to make life behave better
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.36,0:41:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is to take something
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.36,0:41:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that is staggeringly complex
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.36,0:41:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and boil it down to its inner
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.36,0:41:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,inner principles
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.44,0:41:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,simplicity out of complexity
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.44,0:41:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,if a thing is too complex
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.23,0:41:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it just can't be handled
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.23,0:41:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and it gets discarded
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.32,0:41:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,discarded
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.61,0:41:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that's all
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.51,0:41:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's why
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.61,0:41:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.61,0:41:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking about
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.80,0:41:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the language
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.71,0:41:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,algebra
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.71,0:41:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a good friend of mine
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.71,0:41:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is struggling through
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.71,0:41:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,college algebra
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.71,0:41:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's like
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.71,0:41:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,oh god
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.73,0:41:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,it's your karma
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.73,0:41:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,well
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.73,0:41:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you know
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.73,0:41:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,struggling through
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.73,0:41:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,college algebra
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.96,0:41:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I gotta say
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.96,0:41:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that is really
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.00,0:42:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe one of the maximum
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.00,0:42:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,things you gotta live through
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.03,0:42:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.03,0:42:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a rite of passage
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.03,0:42:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't until you complete
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.92,0:42:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't anything good to know
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.30,0:42:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that algebra can serve you in today's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.40,0:42:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got a computer that'll do it that fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.26,0:42:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't even written it down to start figuring it out,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.38,0:42:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and the computer's got it already.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.55,0:42:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you going to do with college algebra?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.86,0:42:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's a rite of passage.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.09,0:42:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rite of passage.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.40,0:42:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You just can't get there without doing college algebra.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.19,0:42:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And instantly you get sympathy from everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.80,0:42:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, what are you doing tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.73,0:42:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, I'm studying college algebra.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.88,0:42:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And you all go, oh, geez.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.30,0:42:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me give you a piece of pie to take home something
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.96,0:42:56.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to make up for having to study college algebra all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.09,0:42:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rite of passage,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.78,0:43:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course it's out in the limits of usefulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.78,0:43:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Any computer can do it in a one-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.78,0:43:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What takes you all?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.94,0:43:07.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the evening computer can do it in no time at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.78,0:43:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So life moves on from complexity to simplicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.40,0:43:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So that which was undoable through complexity
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.61,0:43:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is now doable through simplicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.40,0:43:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So we try to simplify life's problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.42,0:43:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's move on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.82,0:43:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Realistic expectations of life and of others and of events.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.38,0:43:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you realistically expect?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.63,0:43:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're going to be interested in politics,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.09,0:43:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to modify your expectations.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.92,0:43:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If you expect honesty and integrity and all that, forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.78,0:43:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Just get realistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.53,0:43:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in a different world with different values.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.65,0:43:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the thing is you cannot judge their world by your world.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.44,0:43:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've had to struggle through that myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.26,0:44:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Their world is not your world.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.07,0:44:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In their world, making it happen,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.32,0:44:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and if it takes a few bucks here and a few bucks there,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.19,0:44:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not your world.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.21,0:44:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not your world.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.28,0:44:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not your world.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.32,0:44:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If it takes a few bucks there and lying here and testifying falsely,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.00,0:44:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what their game is about.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.30,0:44:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't use your rules and put it in their domain
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.17,0:44:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,because in their domain, you would be an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.11,0:44:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So values then are contextual,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.73,0:44:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,depend on who you are and where you are in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.03,0:44:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, we can't judge others.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.94,0:44:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Value is in the eye of the beholder.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.51,0:44:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What you think of is the eye of the beholder.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.76,0:44:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What you think is valuable is what's valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.05,0:44:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to give up your skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.82,0:44:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,As we said, you can be skeptical about anything except you're skeptical.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.23,0:44:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Your skepticism, in a sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.42,0:45:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And a sense of humor serves you in all of these.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.96,0:45:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,101 ways to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.61,0:45:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All of them are enhanced by a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.19,0:45:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.26,0:45:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Accept karmic propensity.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.76,0:45:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Many things are karmic.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.01,0:45:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This means a propensity, a tendency.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.80,0:45:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not cause and effect, but a likelihood.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.00,0:45:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And when we investigated it with consciousness research,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.44,0:45:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a high likelihood.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.55,0:45:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have a lot of negative karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.65,0:45:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't that the negative karma causes the earthquake to happen just where you live,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.34,0:45:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but because you have that karma, you happen to be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.07,0:45:46.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a propensity, not a causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.90,0:45:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma doesn't cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.63,0:45:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't cause anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.11,0:45:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But the likelihood of certain things happening is certainly being enhanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.19,0:45:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,See essence rather than perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.50,0:46:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the wolf in sheep's clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.71,0:46:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Be jocular instead of morose.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.13,0:46:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Jocular instead of morose.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.44,0:46:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What's 41?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.23,0:46:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Good will regarding all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.48,0:46:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is the one that pays off the most.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.19,0:46:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Good will regarding all of life makes all of us happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.28,0:46:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Good will regarding all of life makes all of the rest of these easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.84,0:46:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All you need is that one and a hundred other ways to be happy come about.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.65,0:46:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If somebody ate your hamburger when you went to the man's room,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.30,0:46:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd say, well, I guess he was hungry and didn't have any money.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.67,0:46:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Good will regarding all of life makes all of them easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.34,0:46:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,To be easygoing, uplifting, easygoing versus rigid.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.11,0:47:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can do that by reducing expectations of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.30,0:47:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't expect anything of them at all, you're never disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.11,0:47:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If somebody's integrous, honest, intelligent, and educated, I fall over.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.07,0:47:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.26,0:47:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Reduce your expectations of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.07,0:47:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've mentioned before that if you have good will towards all of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.03,0:47:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll see what a...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.71,0:47:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,an effect you have on people.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.96,0:47:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always say, when you're in a store and they ring you up on the cash register,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.94,0:47:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you thank them very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.42,0:47:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, thank you a lot for racking that all up.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.30,0:47:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And they'll go, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.63,0:47:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They do it hundreds of times before somebody says, thank you for ringing that up.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.84,0:47:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Reduce your expectations of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.67,0:47:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Be generous instead of stingy.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.46,0:47:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Generous with what?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.09,0:47:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Generous with yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.15,0:48:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Not generous with...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.55,0:48:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,one thing or another.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.11,0:48:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Generosity is an attitude towards life.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.50,0:48:07.59,Default,,0,0,0,,A givingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.65,0:48:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A nurturance.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.65,0:48:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You're generous towards all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.96,0:48:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You walk through the woods and you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.63,0:48:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,my God, these trees are magnificent and beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.40,0:48:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I love the trees in the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.03,0:48:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I adore them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.73,0:48:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's see.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.82,0:48:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Our person asks this.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.57,0:48:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The trees in the woods are...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.36,0:48:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,know that I'm glad and love them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.73,0:48:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The trees...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.21,0:48:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in the woods know that you love them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.63,0:48:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All of life falls down before that which is loving and reflects God's love.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.30,0:48:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, the woods, the trees are literally aware of your lovingness of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.82,0:48:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.65,0:48:58.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All of life then responds to what you...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.38,0:49:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,not what you have, not what you do, not what you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.57,0:49:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but what you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.36,0:49:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What affects?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.80,0:49:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole world.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.61,0:49:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,People say, what can I do to save the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.67,0:49:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, stay out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.11,0:49:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay home.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.75,0:49:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay out of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.96,0:49:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep away from parades and demonstrations.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.51,0:49:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You have...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.76,0:49:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all of us affect the consciousness level of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.23,0:49:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you do to bring about world peace?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.84,0:49:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, avoid peace marches.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.05,0:49:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, become as generous and loving as you can towards all of life in all its regard.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.30,0:49:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, as you step over the little bug, instead of stomping it,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.05,0:49:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you have not done more for the world than parading around with banners.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.46,0:49:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What you...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.71,0:49:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The way you affect what all of life is about
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.34,0:49:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is by the virtue of what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.32,0:50:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.40,0:50:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What you have become.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.84,0:50:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Not what you say, not what you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.40,0:50:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All of that's trivial.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.11,0:50:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, I'm getting threats.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.03,0:50:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, uh, could I have a hand on that, Loewen?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.92,0:50:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we stop here for now?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.55,0:50:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them what, what, how long.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.63,0:50:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll resume at two o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.01,0:50:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You tell them that.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.38,0:50:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be taking a lunch break and we'll be resuming at two o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.59,0:50:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.36,0:50:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hear it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.65,0:51:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All good things come to he who waits.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.51,0:51:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.90,0:51:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All good things come to he who waits.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.65,0:51:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we ready to resume?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.13,0:51:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.73,0:51:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, then what we need is the excitement of the upcoming slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.96,0:51:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, you'll have to wait a minute because I don't know if Janice is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.57,0:51:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.32,0:52:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, we'll talk about a good karma savings account.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.65,0:52:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, everyone needs a good karma savings account.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.73,0:52:14.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you do something that the world considers good,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.76,0:52:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, you don't expect an immediate reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.82,0:52:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be, uh, saintly and have all kinds of horrible things happen to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.80,0:52:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Because, uh, because of the goodness,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.05,0:52:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you, you've brought up the privilege of, um, owning the negative, the bad karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.94,0:52:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see that you rise above your good karma and then that brings up the bad karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.67,0:52:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if bad things are happening to you, you thank God that I've got the good karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.48,0:52:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring up that bad karma, to work it through.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.19,0:53:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.11,0:53:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,My thumb karma is settled.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.71,0:53:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody needs a good karma savings account.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.11,0:53:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A good karma savings account.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.94,0:53:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you need it, it's there for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.90,0:53:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's ask the arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.01,0:53:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.26,0:53:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.40,0:53:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.55,0:53:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Many, uh, things that were totally beyond the expectation or even possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.42,0:53:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,or even a possibility, happened under very strange circumstances in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.01,0:53:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember being a million miles from nowhere in a strange country where I didn't know a soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.96,0:53:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And I got my old truck and the truck, all of a sudden, it broke down.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.98,0:54:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There I'm a million miles, nobody, uh, within sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.00,0:54:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm sitting there with this truck and I think there was something missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.84,0:54:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't take the tire off anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.53,0:54:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, so I sat there.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.00,0:54:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.34,0:54:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.46,0:54:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden, the car peers out of the distance and it was an old buddy from back east.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.86,0:54:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,An old buddy from back east just happened to drive on this deserted highway
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.28,0:54:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and find me, the only person along this way for miles,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.13,0:54:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,broken down with the need for help with my truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.71,0:54:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Another time, I broke down on a clover leaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.34,0:54:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was due at the airport, I think, someplace important.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.09,0:54:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And the car, and, and,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.78,0:54:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and it drove, you know, it was the same old truck, broke down on a clover leaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.26,0:54:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My good karma truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.69,0:54:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it broke down on a clover leaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.61,0:55:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, here's all these cars whizzing by you like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.40,0:55:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And here I'm in this old truck stuck over to the side, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.48,0:55:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden, the car pulled over.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.11,0:55:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was a pickup truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.94,0:55:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Guy gets out and he says to me, I see you're broken down and you got a spare.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.94,0:55:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, no, I'll have to get this one fixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.19,0:55:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, I'll help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.32,0:55:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He took the, he did the thing, took the tire off, put it in the back of his pickup truck.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.21,0:55:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, I'll be back.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.01,0:55:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He went down this clover leaf all the way up and all the way down and all the way back around again.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.57,0:55:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And went off down and got, oh, here, went to a filling station and got the, got the tire fixed.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.57,0:55:44.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he came all the way back through the clover leaf and all the way back, all the way back this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.13,0:55:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And all the way back, and he pulled up next to me and he put it on the truck for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.51,0:55:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Complete, total stranger.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.76,0:55:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought, my God, what is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.57,0:55:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And he says, thanks, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.69,0:55:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.88,0:55:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,God bless you.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.44,0:56:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was the end of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.21,0:56:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.96,0:56:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,That was my good karma savings account.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.82,0:56:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I learned something else too.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.36,0:56:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There are angels in bodies.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.80,0:56:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Some residents of this domain are angelic, are actually angels and have taken on a human energy fuel for purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.90,0:56:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if you've heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.82,0:56:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if you've heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:39.96,0:56:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if you've heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.19,0:56:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if you've heard of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.71,0:56:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.86,0:56:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, those things, those are things that having a positive karma savings account, I mean, it was unthinkable.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.94,0:56:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A million miles from nowhere and nobody even knew I was in Arizona.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.73,0:57:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's an old friend from back, he pulls right up, right next to my car and says, can I help you and takes the tire off for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.92,0:57:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of a clover leaf with all these millions of cars going by, this guy comes in, picks it up, takes it down, goes all the way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:10.13,0:57:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,As it's fixed, comes over.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.30,0:57:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the way back around and picks me up again. I mean, that's inexplicable by logic, by any kind
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.19,0:57:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of logic. So the good that you do to others, don't look for a reward. Just give this as a gift to
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.57,0:57:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,God. So what I do, I do for you out of my love for God. And then later on, it comes back to you
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.71,0:57:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in some unforeseen and non-logical connection, you know. And so we serve others to the best of
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.44,0:57:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,our ability, and we surrender that to God. Yes. All right. Now, are we going to show the slides?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.48,0:58:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Are they going to? I put a quarter in the slot before. There it is. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.19,0:58:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a thingy here. Here it is. All right. What was on that card? I didn't want to forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.48,0:58:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Oh, no. Okay. All right. So I just wanted to put that one in there. That wasn't on the list.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.48,0:58:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Accumulate good karma. All right. Goodwill regarding all of life. To be of goodwill to
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.40,0:58:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,all of life, then is noticed by all of life. You think it's not noticed, it's noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.40,0:58:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And that builds up your positive karma bank. To be loving towards all the trees,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.36,0:58:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to be loving.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.98,0:59:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,towards the bugs, to be of goodwill towards all that exists, to have an easygoing attitude
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.55,0:59:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of rigid. It doesn't have to be your way or no way. It's just easygoing means being
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.28,0:59:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,flexible, and things are not always going to go the way you go, so you'd be willing to
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.90,0:59:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,change. To be generous instead of stingy. Generous of what? Generosity is an attitude. It's not
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.76,0:59:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,monetary. It can take a monetary expression, but generosity is an attitude. Generous towards all
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.80,0:59:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of life. Generous in your expectations. Thanking people for being of service
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.82,0:59:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,at the church.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.05,1:00:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Checkout counter at the supermarket. You say, thank you for running that up. Thank you for
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.36,1:00:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,running that. A lot of times, if you do that, you'll see their mouth drops. They say, what?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.11,1:00:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for totaling that all up. Oh, okay. Generous instead of stingy.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.32,1:00:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Modify the inner voice so that it reflects your spiritual attitudes. You know, you go inside to
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.36,1:00:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,your inner thoughts, and you talk to your inner thoughts until you've gotten,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.01,1:00:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,your inner voice to be reflective of your spiritual commitment and intention. To be
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.92,1:00:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,gracious to self and others. Be gracious. That's part of generosity. To be gracious to yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.96,1:00:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and others. Well, we often remember to be gracious to others, but here's where we, most of us,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.53,1:00:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,be gracious to yourself. I thank you, Lord, for my existence and all the wondrous and
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.09,1:01:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,wonderful things that have happened to me and the wonderful people I've met. So you be gracious to
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.88,1:01:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself. Gracious to others. That, everybody learns sooner or later. But gracious to yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.78,1:01:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,takes quite a while to learn because the self tends to be critical. The inner parent says to
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.32,1:01:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you, naughty, naughty, bad, bad, you were no good. How can you be gracious to yourself, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.09,1:01:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is to have a more easygoing conscience.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.92,1:01:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,More easygoing conscience that understands your humanness. Your humanness. If you were perfect,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.69,1:01:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't be here. So part of perfection is correcting an overly strict superego. The
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.92,1:01:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,first thing, it's one of the first things my psychoanalyst said to me, you know, is laying on the couch.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.69,1:01:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, number one, you've got to have thicker skin. Not be so sensitive to what others say. And secondly,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.28,1:02:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to be more forgiving to yourself, because I had a very rigid superego.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.44,1:02:15.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Rigid superego. What do they call that? Scrupulosity. So the reason I went in, one of the
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.15,1:02:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,reasons I went into psychoanalysis was scrupulosity. And as a child, I had counseling for
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.21,1:02:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,scrupulosity. The sleigh, I lived in fear of the sin, that I might have committed a sin. And I was
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.28,1:02:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,scared to death that my skin would be broken. And so I had to have more forgiveness. And I had to have
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.09,1:02:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,own mind that it would think of sinful thoughts my mother would ask me to do something and i
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.34,1:02:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,would feel anger come up and i lived in dread of that because to be angry at your mother was a sin
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.44,1:02:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,so how do we have a more forgiving inner conscience that one way to have a more
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.61,1:03:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,forgiving inner conscience is to be aware that it's intention so the intention is what you end up
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.57,1:03:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at not the act but the intention behind the act because an act can go wrong even though
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.98,1:03:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,your intention is good so you develop a more flexible easygoing loving and forgiving
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.19,1:03:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so love everyone and don't forget to include yourself in that as well surrender the need
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.98,1:03:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to control others the need to control and surrendering that is not necessary to control
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.32,1:03:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that happens to you
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.94,1:03:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world it's not necessary to control it so it's the feeling that you have to change things
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.73,1:03:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have to control them that you have to be on top of them and you become much more easygoing
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.38,1:03:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not necessary to control everything that happens in life because there's positive karma
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.34,1:04:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that will correct many a thing yeah all you need to do is hold what you desire and value in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.88,1:04:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and it tends to manifest within your life
